      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "@Tim 'mithro' Ansell This is the project I wish to use to officially test my SCL, as well as my multi-project setup using my SCL. I’m also using the level-shifting IO pads, but for having a 5V IO voltage and 3.3V core voltage, which should be interesting. Also has layouts generated by my custom flow tool, *analog* layouts meant for 3.3V operation and, of course, a bunch of CPUs.\nHoping to get a lot of mileage out of this one when it comes to testing things.",
